<HEADLINE>
KMT CHIEF INDICTED FOR CORRUPTION
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Feb. 13 (CNA) 02/13/07  15:43:49 (By Maubo Chang)
</P>
<P>
Kuomintang (KMT) Chairman Ma Ying-jeou was formally indicted on
corruption charges Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ma was charged with lining his pockets during his term as Taipei
City's mayor with NT$11 million (US$332,684) from a special
allowance fund set aside for the mayor's discretionary use.
</P>
<P>
One of Ma's aides, Yu Wen, who allegedly used others' invoices to
help Ma to claim reimbursements from the special allowance fund,
was also indicted for embezzling NT$760,000 from the special
allowance fund.
</P>
<P>
Five other city government officials who had allegedly provided
Yu with their invoices were handed deferred indictments on
forgery charges.
</P>
